      "content": "It makes perfect sense that losing those primary sources of your joy feels like losing yourself entirely. When your core creative drive is gone, the motivation to move forward can feel nonexistent. Please consider speaking with a therapist who can help you explore this transition and build new sources of meaning, even if they don't look like your old art or music. Remember that your value as a person isn't solely defined by what you create.",
      "source": "target",
